UK Reform is US Conservative.

There has been a drift in the US. &quot;Orthodox&quot; has been drifting toward the
right, shading, from right to left of  Hassidim, black hats and Young
Israel. &quot;Conservative&quot; has been moving like tectonic plates, with
&quot;Traditional Conservative&quot; differing from Modern Orthodox only in the
seating in the sanctuary. Egalitarian Conservative is now distance from
Traditional.

Wedged in between Reform and Egalitarian Conservative is Reconstructionist.
Then further to the left is Reform, which ranges from Kashruth and Shabbat
observance to Liberal Reform. In the UK, I attended a Liberal service that
resembled left-wing US Conservative.

&quot;It's enough to cross a rabbi's eyes.&quot;

Leon

PS. In response to an e-mail inquiry, when I was a newspaperman (no, I
didn't sell old newspapers, I wrote them), the style we used required that
we capitalize the R in rabbi or C in congregation when using it as a name,
as in &quot;When the rabbi spoke, he told the congregation that Rabbi Cohen would
be leading Congregation Etz Chaim next week.&quot;
